# FIX (deploy-cache issue): this app is a single static index.html with no
# hashed filename per build, so Netlify's default asset caching (and
# intermediate browser/CDN caches) kept serving the previous deploy's copy
# until a visitor did a manual hard refresh. Forcing no-store here means
# every visit re-fetches the latest deployed HTML.
/*
  Cache-Control: no-cache, no-store, must-revalidate
